228
00:17:14.535 --> 00:17:18.747
<i># The flowers reaching
for the sun #

229
00:17:18.830 --> 00:17:22.459
# Are all uniquely blessed #

230
00:17:22.501 --> 00:17:26.547
# But though each is special #

231
00:17:26.630 --> 00:17:30.634
# Not a one is better #

232
00:17:30.676 --> 00:17:33.387
<i># Than the rest #

233
00:17:34.471 --> 00:17:38.684
# Bloom. bloom May you know #

234
00:17:38.725 --> 00:17:43.438
# The wisdom only time breeds #

235
00:17:43.522 --> 00:17:48.569
<i># There's room. bloom
and you'll grow #

236
00:17:48.652 --> 00:17:53.824
<i># To follow where your heart leads #

237
00:17:53.866 --> 00:17:57.995
# Bloom and may you bring #

238
00:17:58.036 --> 00:18:03.166
# Your colors to the vast bouquet #

239
00:18:03.208 --> 00:18:07.504
# There's room. bloom Learn one thing #

240
00:18:07.546 --> 00:18:16.013
# Your gifts are meant to give away #

241
00:18:16.054 --> 00:18:18.015
Thanks. Mom.

242
00:18:32.946 --> 00:18:35.532
Judah! Simeon!

243
00:18:35.574 --> 00:18:37.534
Levi! Reuben!

244
00:18:37.576 --> 00:18:39.536
Where are you?

245
00:18:39.578 --> 00:18:41.872
-<i>Joseph isn't fit to lead sheep.
- I agree.

246
00:18:41.914 --> 00:18:44.374
-<i>But he's our brother.
- Half brother.

247
00:18:44.458 --> 00:18:47.294
<i>Said so himself.Judah is the one
who should take over for Father.

248
00:18:47.377 --> 00:18:50.214
Yes. but... Do you want a spoiled brat
giving you orders?

249
00:18:50.255 --> 00:18:54.092
No. Can we all agree that something
has to be done aboutJoseph?

250
00:18:54.176 --> 00:18:56.845
- Absolutely.
- Yes. I agree.

251
00:18:56.929 --> 00:18:59.890
- <i>Hey. everybody! The little spy is back!
- I wasn't spying.

252
00:18:59.932 --> 00:19:02.809
- Did Father tell you to check up on us?
- No! Maybe this was a mistake.

253
00:19:02.893 --> 00:19:05.145
- I just want to--
- Report on us to Father?

254
00:19:05.229 --> 00:19:07.814
- You're his favorite.
- N-No.

255
00:19:07.898 --> 00:19:11.485
You look at scrolls all day
while we're covered in sweat.

256
00:19:11.568 --> 00:19:14.821
Why is that.Joseph? Is it because
we don't have pretty coats like you?

257
00:19:14.905 --> 00:19:17.824
- I have mine.
- That's my coat!

258
00:19:17.908 --> 00:19:21.286
Step aside. brothers.
I'm the new head of the family.

259
00:19:21.370 --> 00:19:24.623
<i>Bow before me.
you sheaves of wheat!

260
00:19:24.706 --> 00:19:27.042
Oh. yes. MasterJoseph.
ruler of the world.

261
00:19:27.125 --> 00:19:28.794
Give it back. now!

262
00:19:28.877 --> 00:19:32.714
If you want your coat.
why don't you go get it?

263
00:19:32.798 --> 00:19:36.093
- Levi's got it.
- No. I don't.Judah does.

264
00:19:36.134 --> 00:19:38.220
- <i>Come on!
- I've got it!

265
00:19:44.518 --> 00:19:47.521
- I've had enough of this stupid game!
-<i>Joseph!

266
00:19:47.604 --> 00:19:49.606
Who says this is a game?

267
00:19:51.817 --> 00:19:55.946
What are you doing? Leave me alone!
No! Stop it!

268
00:19:59.116 --> 00:20:01.451
Oh! Ohh!

269
00:20:08.667 --> 00:20:11.295
<i>What do we do now?

270
00:20:11.336 --> 00:20:14.756
<i>Are we just going to leave him?
What are we going to tell Father?

271
00:20:14.840 --> 00:20:17.092
- We'll think of something.
- Somebody!

272
00:20:17.176 --> 00:20:19.303
- <i>Please!
- Just get out of here.

273
00:20:19.386 --> 00:20:22.723
Maybe he can dream
his way out.

274
00:20:25.267 --> 00:20:27.227
Don't leave me here alone!

275
00:20:48.874 --> 00:20:50.584
Aah! Aah!

276
00:20:59.051 --> 00:21:01.762
Huh?

277
00:21:05.015 --> 00:21:07.100
I knew you'd come back.

278
00:21:12.523 --> 00:21:17.069
You think this is funny? Well.
Father won't be laughing when he hear--

279
00:21:17.152 --> 00:21:19.196
- Who are you?
- Get him.

280
00:21:19.279 --> 00:21:22.074
Hey! Hey!
What are you doing? Ow!

281
00:21:22.115 --> 00:21:26.036
Let me go! You don't understand.
I'm from the house ofJacob.

282
00:21:26.078 --> 00:21:29.206
- A little scrawny. isn't he?
- It's hard to tell with that pretty coat on.

283
00:21:31.333 --> 00:21:34.378
- Hmm.
- No. no. no. don't take my--

284
00:21:34.419 --> 00:21:37.464
Get up!

285
00:21:37.548 --> 00:21:41.301
Looks like he's never worked
a day in his life.

286
00:21:41.385 --> 00:21:43.470
That'll change.

287
00:21:43.554 --> 00:21:46.723
My brothers will come for me.
Judah!

288
00:21:46.765 --> 00:21:50.102
- Simeon! Levi! Please help me!
-<i>Joseph!

289
00:21:50.143 --> 00:21:52.813
We're right here.

290
00:21:52.896 --> 00:21:55.148
Judah.

291
00:21:59.611 --> 00:22:01.989
I told you they'd come for me.

292
00:22:04.241 --> 00:22:07.828
As agreed. 20 pieces of silver.

293
00:22:12.708 --> 00:22:15.210
J- Judah-- Why--

294
00:22:19.131 --> 00:22:22.092
No! Help me!

295
00:22:22.134 --> 00:22:25.012
Levi. please.
Issachar.

296
00:22:25.095 --> 00:22:27.306
Simeon. Stop them.

297
00:22:27.347 --> 00:22:30.184
Judah.Judah. help me. please.

298
00:22:30.267 --> 00:22:32.186
Please!

299
00:22:39.401 --> 00:22:43.155
Judah. please!

300
00:22:43.197 --> 00:22:47.492
Judah. we can't turn back now.
We've gone too far.

301
00:22:47.534 --> 00:22:49.828
- Aah!
- Hut. hut!

302
00:22:52.956 --> 00:22:55.667
I'm your brother!

303
00:22:55.709 --> 00:22:59.171
<i>I'm your brother!

304
00:22:59.213 --> 00:23:01.882
Half brother.

305
00:23:01.965 --> 00:23:04.384
<i>Yah!

306
00:23:42.548 --> 00:23:45.592
- Where could he have gone?
- Don't worry.

307
00:23:45.676 --> 00:23:48.554
I'm sure he's all right.

308
00:23:48.595 --> 00:23:50.931
The boys will find him.

309
00:23:51.014 --> 00:23:53.433
<i>Father.

310
00:23:54.518 --> 00:23:57.229
This is all we found.

311
00:23:58.605 --> 00:24:00.649
Joseph!

312
00:24:00.732 --> 00:24:03.318
- No! Joseph!
- Joseph!

313
00:24:06.071 --> 00:24:08.699
Oh. Rachel.

314
00:24:10.742 --> 00:24:13.412
Hey. wake up.

315
00:24:51.533 --> 00:24:53.952
<i># Behold the glory Behold the wonder #

316
00:24:53.994 --> 00:24:58.081
<i># What we have made
shall not be torn asunder #

317
00:24:58.123 --> 00:25:01.126
<i># Such vast achievement
Stone and papyrus #

318
00:25:01.168 --> 00:25:04.046
<i># Beneath the gaze
of Isis and Osiris #

319
00:25:04.129 --> 00:25:07.382
<i># Land of majesty #

320
00:25:07.466 --> 00:25:11.428
<i># Where the heavens smile #

321
00:25:11.512 --> 00:25:15.015
<i># Jewel of history shining #

322
00:25:15.098 --> 00:25:18.477
<i># By the Nile #

323
00:25:18.519 --> 00:25:21.188
- Hey!
- Here.

324
00:25:23.774 --> 00:25:25.734
- Exquisite. aren't they?
- Yes.

325
00:25:25.817 --> 00:25:28.654
- Where's the slave market?
- Down by the docks.

326
00:25:31.990 --> 00:25:34.660
<i># Serve and be silent #

327
00:25:34.743 --> 00:25:36.870
<i># You who are chattel #

328
00:25:36.954 --> 00:25:39.498
<i># We think of you
as little more than cattle #

329
00:25:39.581 --> 00:25:42.626
-<i># This is your lot now And we advise you #
- Slaves for sale!

330
00:25:42.668 --> 00:25:45.963
<i># To bow before
whatever master buys you #

331
00:25:46.004 --> 00:25:49.508
<i># Feel the power here #

332
00:25:49.591 --> 00:25:52.469
-<i># Power has its price #
- Let's go.

333
00:25:52.511 --> 00:25:55.722
<i># Some can live like gods #

334
00:25:55.806 --> 00:25:59.810
-<i># Some must sacrifice #
- What do you have?

335
00:25:59.893 --> 00:26:01.687
- A Canaanite.
-<i># Through the centuries #

336
00:26:01.728 --> 00:26:05.440
<i># Many backs have bent #

337
00:26:05.524 --> 00:26:07.484
<i># Many dreams are built #

338
00:26:07.526 --> 00:26:11.655
-<i># Many lives are spent #
- Move. slave!

339
00:26:11.697 --> 00:26:13.657
Get in line.

340
00:26:13.699 --> 00:26:17.119
<i>Slaves for sale!
Buy this one!

341
00:26:17.202 --> 00:26:20.581
<i>Now. let's have a look at him.
Let me see his teeth.

342
00:26:20.664 --> 00:26:23.667
Hmm. Mm-hmm.

343
00:26:23.750 --> 00:26:26.545
He's too skinny.

344
00:26:26.628 --> 00:26:29.882
This is more like it.

345
00:26:29.923 --> 00:26:34.011
The captain of the guard needs a slave
for his household. I have one you might like.

346
00:26:35.596 --> 00:26:37.598
Thirty pieces? Hmm.

347
00:26:37.681 --> 00:26:40.893
He looks healthy enough.
Lord Potiphar!

348
00:26:42.603 --> 00:26:47.441
- He'll do.
- Ah. Looks like we have some work to do.

349
00:26:47.524 --> 00:26:51.904
<i># Look and be humbled Learn what
your place is Egyptian slave #

350
00:26:51.987 --> 00:26:54.364
-<i># No matter what your race is #
- Over there.

351
00:26:54.406 --> 00:26:57.409
<i># This is your future
Your life suspended #

352
00:26:57.492 --> 00:27:00.579
<i># And everything
you knew before has ended #

353
00:27:00.662 --> 00:27:04.291
<i># You are Egypt's now #

354
00:27:04.374 --> 00:27:07.753
-<i># We have all control #
- Hey!

355
00:27:07.794 --> 00:27:11.298
-<i># From your every step #
- Aah!

356
00:27:11.381 --> 00:27:13.759
-<i># To your very soul ##
- Hold still.

357
00:27:13.842 --> 00:27:16.553
You're done.
He's ready for work.

358
00:27:28.565 --> 00:27:31.652
<i>It's not for your face.
It's for the floor.

359
00:27:39.326 --> 00:27:41.578
Ow!

360
00:27:44.915 --> 00:27:48.001
Hey. Joseph. you missed a spot.

361
00:27:48.085 --> 00:27:50.587
- What?
-<i>It's different doing real work. isn't it?

362
00:27:50.629 --> 00:27:54.842
- No more baby soft hands.
- Who bows now. little brother?

363
00:28:02.015 --> 00:28:03.976
<i>You there.

364
00:28:05.978 --> 00:28:08.605
Have you cleaned
this entire courtyard by yourself?

365
00:28:08.689 --> 00:28:11.525
- Yes.
-<i>He's a hard worker.

366
00:28:11.608 --> 00:28:14.027
Hmm.

367
00:28:14.111 --> 00:28:17.072
Maybe we could put him to better use
in the banquet hall.

368
00:28:17.155 --> 00:28:20.742
My wife thinks you should work for her.
What do you say?

369
00:28:20.826 --> 00:28:23.078
I cannot say.

370
00:28:23.161 --> 00:28:25.330
A slave is not his own master.

371
00:28:26.582 --> 00:28:28.625
Well said.

372
00:28:28.667 --> 00:28:32.212
Find him some new clothes.
Then get someone else to finish here.

373
00:28:32.296 --> 00:28:34.339
<i>Yes. my lord.

374
00:28:45.100 --> 00:28:49.021
Here. kitty. kitty. kitty! Come on.

375
00:28:49.104 --> 00:28:52.608
<i>Who brought the cat?

376
00:28:52.691 --> 00:28:55.527
- Here. kitty. kitty. kitty.
- Oh. stop that.

377
00:28:55.569 --> 00:28:57.863
<i>Come down!

378
00:28:57.905 --> 00:29:00.991
<i>Aunt Zuleika. I'm sorry.
I'll get it down from there.

379
00:29:01.033 --> 00:29:03.493
<i>Please come down.

380
00:29:03.535 --> 00:29:05.579
<i>Come here. kitty.

381
00:29:05.662 --> 00:29:08.790
Come here.
Look at this.

382
00:29:08.874 --> 00:29:11.043
<i>Oh.

383
00:29:11.126 --> 00:29:14.546
Hmm. She seems to like you.

384
00:29:14.588 --> 00:29:17.841
Thank you.

385
00:29:17.883 --> 00:29:20.844
I haven't seen you here before.

386
00:29:20.886 --> 00:29:23.013
- Oh. I'm new.
-<i>Asenath.

387
00:29:23.055 --> 00:29:27.017
Coming. Aunt Zuleika.
Good-bye.

388
00:29:34.858 --> 00:29:37.027
<i>Joseph. come here.

389
00:29:37.069 --> 00:29:39.196
I'm waiting.

390
00:29:39.238 --> 00:29:41.740
I'm coming!

391
00:29:43.575 --> 00:29:46.537
- Oh! Sorry. Asenath.
- Oh!

392
00:29:46.578 --> 00:29:50.999
What?  I don't think you want
my aunt seeing you like this.

393
00:29:51.083 --> 00:29:53.293
- That's better.
- Thanks.

394
00:29:53.377 --> 00:29:55.379
Slave.

395
00:29:55.462 --> 00:29:58.882
Oh. yes. of course.

396
00:30:02.803 --> 00:30:06.640
Hyah! Hyah!

397
00:30:06.723 --> 00:30:09.685
<i>What a magnificent animal.

398
00:30:09.768 --> 00:30:12.896
<i>Faster. Faster. Ah!

399
00:30:12.980 --> 00:30:15.065
Slave.

400
00:30:15.148 --> 00:30:17.317
- I'm in the sun.
- <i>Hyah! Ho!

401
00:30:20.737 --> 00:30:22.906
Whoa!

402
00:30:22.948 --> 00:30:26.118
- Well?
- You were right.

403
00:30:26.201 --> 00:30:30.038
He's all that you promised. I haven't seen
a finer horse in all of Egypt.

404
00:30:30.122 --> 00:30:32.457
I'm glad Your Excellency
is pleased.

405
00:30:32.499 --> 00:30:37.462
- There is still one small matter.
- Oh. yes. As we agreed.

406
00:30:44.303 --> 00:30:47.848
Oh. forgive me. but something
is not quite right.  Hmm.

407
00:30:47.931 --> 00:30:50.392
I thought I brought
the right amount.

408
00:30:50.475 --> 00:30:53.896
<i>You're a busy man.
Anyone can make a mistake.

409
00:30:57.858 --> 00:31:01.445
He's yours.
Pharaoh himself would be jealous.

410
00:31:01.486 --> 00:31:03.739
<i>Yes. he's a fine horse.

411
00:31:03.822 --> 00:31:06.158
Hmm.

412
00:31:06.241 --> 00:31:09.995
Master. I think you should see this.

413
00:31:10.037 --> 00:31:13.624
Uh-- Get away from that.
Don't touch it!

414
00:31:13.707 --> 00:31:15.667
Well. look at that.

415
00:31:15.751 --> 00:31:18.504
Well. I--
It's broken.

416
00:31:18.587 --> 00:31:21.798
- Your Excellency. I had no idea.
- Of course not.

417
00:31:21.840 --> 00:31:25.010
You're a busy man.
Anyone can make a mistake.

418
00:31:25.093 --> 00:31:27.679
And yours is going
to cost you your freedom.

419
00:31:27.763 --> 00:31:30.390
Please. keep the stallion
as a gift from me.

420
00:31:30.474 --> 00:31:34.353
No. Take him away.

421
00:31:34.394 --> 00:31:37.064
<i>I have a dozen more horses!
Take them all!

422
00:31:37.147 --> 00:31:39.358
Please. anything!

423
00:31:39.441 --> 00:31:41.860
Potiphar.
you should keep it.

424
00:31:41.944 --> 00:31:44.363
You said it was the finest
in all Egypt.

425
00:31:44.446 --> 00:31:49.868
Own a horse taken from a thief?
What would that say about my honor?

426
00:31:49.952 --> 00:31:51.787
You and your honor.

427
00:31:53.038 --> 00:31:55.999
- You've done well. What's your name?
- Joseph.

428
00:31:56.083 --> 00:31:59.628
Joseph.
You're an educated slave.

429
00:31:59.711 --> 00:32:02.881
- Where did you learn?
- My father taught me.

430
00:32:02.923 --> 00:32:05.884
Ah. He taught you well.

431
00:32:05.968 --> 00:32:11.223
Tell me what else your father has taught you.
I can read and write Egyptian.

432
00:32:11.306 --> 00:32:14.017
<i># A boy looks up #

433
00:32:14.059 --> 00:32:17.354
-<i># And sees a golden gift of chance #
- What a mess.

434
00:32:17.396 --> 00:32:19.773
Good luck.

435
00:32:19.857 --> 00:32:22.442
<i># To prove his worth #

436
00:32:22.526 --> 00:32:26.446
<i># And make the best
of what might seem #

437
00:32:26.530 --> 00:32:29.283
<i># A dire circumstance #

438
00:32:29.366 --> 00:32:33.579
<i># Onward and onward
the slow and steady climb #

439
00:32:33.620 --> 00:32:36.039
- Master.
- Let's have a look.

440
00:32:37.708 --> 00:32:40.794
<i># Task upon task
that can lift him #

441
00:32:40.878 --> 00:32:44.381
-<i># To the summit over time #
- Well done.Joseph.

442
00:32:44.423 --> 00:32:48.385
<i># You've got to take whatever
road's at your feet #

443
00:32:48.427 --> 00:32:53.015
<i># You've got to make
whatever progress you can #

444
00:32:53.098 --> 00:32:57.227
<i># Although the map you hold
is far from complete #

445
00:32:57.269 --> 00:33:02.441
<i># You've got to take whatever
road's at your feet ##

446
00:33:08.655 --> 00:33:11.450
To a good year. and to your friend.

447
00:33:42.856 --> 00:33:45.651
My neck is killing me.

448
00:33:45.692 --> 00:33:49.696
<i>It's too early for this.

449
00:34:06.171 --> 00:34:08.340
-<i>Rachel.
- Joseph.

450
00:34:08.423 --> 00:34:11.510
- Huh?
- Shh!

451
00:34:11.593 --> 00:34:15.681
- W-Why are you here? Is something wrong?
- No.

452
00:34:15.764 --> 00:34:19.560
This land--
it's not Egypt.

453
00:34:19.643 --> 00:34:23.313
Is this your home?

454
00:34:23.355 --> 00:34:25.399
- Canaan.
- <i>Please.

455
00:34:25.482 --> 00:34:28.068
tell me more about Canaan.

456
00:34:30.153 --> 00:34:34.575
This is the place where I was born.

457
00:34:34.658 --> 00:34:39.037
These are the sunflowers
my mother planted.

458
00:34:39.079 --> 00:34:41.498
This is my. uh--

459
00:34:41.540 --> 00:34:43.917
- My--
- Family?

460
00:34:44.001 --> 00:34:46.253
You miss them. don't you?

461
00:34:46.336 --> 00:34:48.255
My brothers.

462
00:34:48.338 --> 00:34:50.424
They betrayed me!

463
00:34:50.507 --> 00:34:54.970
- Joseph. we are your family now.
- Huh?

464
00:34:55.053 --> 00:34:57.181
We care for you here.

465
00:34:57.264 --> 00:35:00.601
We-- I feel
you are special.

466
00:35:00.684 --> 00:35:04.354
What? No.
W-Why have you come here tonight?

467
00:35:04.438 --> 00:35:06.398
- To be with you.
- No.

468
00:35:06.440 --> 00:35:08.525
- This is not right.
- Look at me.

469
00:35:08.609 --> 00:35:10.777
- I will not betray my master.
- I'm talking to you.

470
00:35:10.861 --> 00:35:13.363
- No! Stop! No!
- Wait! I order you to stay!

471
00:35:13.447 --> 00:35:16.241
No!

472
00:35:16.283 --> 00:35:18.785
Everything you are. you owe to me!

473
00:35:28.378 --> 00:35:31.089
You stood apart from the other slaves.

474
00:35:31.131 --> 00:35:34.927
I let you work in my home.
I kept you from hard labor.

475
00:35:35.010 --> 00:35:37.346
and you did well for me.

476
00:35:37.429 --> 00:35:39.389
- Or so I thought.
- Master--

477
00:35:39.431 --> 00:35:44.102
No other slave was ever given
this opportunity! I gave you my trust.

478
00:35:44.186 --> 00:35:46.688
- What do you say for yourself?
- I did nothing wrong.

479
00:35:46.772 --> 00:35:49.608
And still you insult me
with your denials!

480
00:35:49.691 --> 00:35:52.736
What am I to make of this?

481
00:35:54.613 --> 00:35:57.741
It's not what it seems.
I could never betray you. master.

482
00:35:57.783 --> 00:36:01.578
Such insolence!
Am I to believe a slave over my own wife?

483
00:36:01.620 --> 00:36:04.623
<i>I swear.
I did nothing to betray you.

484
00:36:04.665 --> 00:36:07.543
Silence!
For what you have done.

485
