that had three old vines.

500
00:37:49.228 --> 00:37:53.524
<i>A tear fell from my eye.
and the vines drank it in.

501
00:37:53.565 --> 00:37:56.401
<i>They became so thick
with grapes...

502
00:37:56.485 --> 00:37:59.571
<i>that I squeezed them into a cup
and served it to Pharaoh.

503
00:37:59.655 --> 00:38:02.574
That is quite a dream.

504
00:38:04.076 --> 00:38:08.664
- I know what your dream means.
- You do? How could you?

505
00:38:08.747 --> 00:38:12.167
I just do.
It's some kind of gift.

506
00:38:12.251 --> 00:38:15.295
The-The three vines
signify three days.

507
00:38:15.379 --> 00:38:19.174
In three days. Pharaoh will bring you
back to the palace a free man.

508
00:38:19.258 --> 00:38:23.220
- If only it were true.
- It is true.

509
00:38:23.303 --> 00:38:27.224
And when you're free. tell Pharaoh
about my gift. Please. Promise me.

510
00:38:27.266 --> 00:38:31.895
Some gift. To make up fairy tales
and give hope to the foolish.

511
00:38:31.979 --> 00:38:35.732
- Maybe he's not making it up.
-<i>All right. then.

512
00:38:35.774 --> 00:38:38.694
Here's one I've had every night
for the last week.

513
00:38:38.777 --> 00:38:42.531
I'm taking three baskets of bread
to Pharaoh. one on top of the other.

514
00:38:42.614 --> 00:38:44.783
<i>when the baskets fall.

515
00:38:44.867 --> 00:38:47.953
<i>I go to pick up the bread. when
suddenly a swarm of birds...

516
00:38:48.036 --> 00:38:50.038
